NEW YORK (AP) — Stocks that traded heavily or had substantial price changes Monday: Spirit Airlines Inc., down $1.95 to $22.57.Frontier Group sweetened its buyout offer for the airline.TreeHouse Foods Inc., up 94 cents to $41.54.The food maker is reportedly considering selling its meal prep business.Devon Energy Corp., up $4.02 to $57.79.Energy companies gained ground along with rising oil prices.Freeport McMoRan Inc., up 3 cents to $31.02.The copper mining company gained ground along with rising prices for the precious metal.United Airlines Holdings Inc., down $1.31 to $37.20.Airlines remain under pressure from scrutiny over widespread flight disruptions.Royal Caribbean Croup, down $1.43 to $40.33.Cruise lines slipped as investors remain concerned about the lingering effects of the pandemic and higher fuel prices on the industry.Pfizer Inc., up 29 cents to $51.88The drug developer said tweaking its COVID-19 vaccine to better target the omicron variant is safe and boosts protection.Walgreens Boots Alliance Inc., up 54 cents to $42.19.Reliance Industries is reportedly in talks with global banks to raise money for a buyout of the drugstore operator’s international business.